In standard SQL (which is how the question is tagged), you would do:

    WHERE HireDate &lt; CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL &#39;15 YEAR&#39;

Date functions are notoriously database-dependent.  So the exact syntax varies by database and this might not work in your particular database.

